data.title: Arsenal ratings from Ostersunds FK defeat as Gunners' fringe players flop on chance to impress
data.meta_description: The likes of Holding and Chambers were particularly disappointing as Arsenal limped through
data.text:
Arsenal were hugely disappointing as they limped into the last 16 of the Europa League despite losing to Swedish minnows Ostersund.

The Gunners led 3-0 from last week's first leg but were well below-par as they fell 2-0 down before the break.

Sead Kolasinac ended the visitors' hopes of a incredible comeback but Arsenal struggled throughout.

For some players it was a chance to impress ahead of the Carabao Cup final but the fringe players blew it.

Here are Darren Lewis' player ratings.

Arsenal

Ospina 6 - No chance with the goals. Exposed by his poor defence.

Bellerin 6 - Good cross from him for the goal to be fair.

Chambers 4 - Unlucky for the first goal but poor for the second.

Holding 4 - No real understanding with Chambers and Ostersunds cashed in.

Kolasinac 7 - Fine finish,minutes into the second half, as Arsenal improved.

Elneny 5 - Good second half strike to force a fine save out of Aly Keita.

Maitland-Niles 4 - Never at the races. Replaced at half time.

Mkhitaryan 5 - Even his classy abilities could not make an impact first half

Wilshere 6 - One of the few to emerge with any credit from this shambles.

Iwobi 5 - Not enough of an impact considering his ability.

Welbeck 5 - Tried - and failed - to chip the keeper with much better options available.

Subs

Xhaka 6 (for Maitland Niles 45)

Willock 5 (for Wilshere 75)
